message.content:
This command establishes a secure shell (SSH) connection to an Amazon EC2 instance with the hostname "ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com" and username "user". The connection is authenticated using a private key file named "UserKey.pem" located in the user's home directory (~).

The command also enables compression (-C) and creates a local forwarded port (L) on the client machine, mapping it to a specific port on the remote EC2 instance. In this case, the local port 25900 is forwarded to the remote port 5900 (VNC/RDP) on the localhost of the remote machine.

This allows the user to connect to the remote VNC/RDP session using the forwarded local port instead of connecting directly to the remote EC2 instance, which can improve network performance and security by keeping the connection within the client's network.
